text: Anarsia taurella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by John David Bradley in 1961. It is found on Guadalcanal.Anarsia at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms The wingspan is about 11 mm. The forewings are cinnamon buff mixed with light clay colour, and with a sprinkling of brown scales in the middle. The hindwings are mouse grey, overlaid with fuscous around the margins and hyaline near base.Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) (Entomology). 10 (4): 134 ==References== taurella Category:Moths described in 1961 Category:Moths of Oceania
title: Anarsia taurella
